---
description: Use these rules for UI tests tasks
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use given (test setup) / when (tested action) / then (assertions) in tests provided as comments // given, // when, // then
- use faker.js for generating random data
- use dedicated pages (objects): see pages/LoginPage.ts and pages/HomePage.ts as examples
- use data-testid attributes for locating elements
- you can use http clients to perform test setup if needed (see http/users/signupRequest.ts and http/users/loginRequest.ts as examples)
- you can use Playwright MCP to find out how UI elements are structured and how to locate them
- do not create too many tests for validatione errors. Assume sufficient unit tests coverage for these cases.
- Once you create new tests run them via Playwright. Make sure they pass, iterate with fixes if needed. If you believe there is a bug in application leave the test as failing and let me know about it
- always run tests in headless mode